article.headline: ETSU 103, Milligan 55
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- Curtis Wilkinson had 15 points and 10 rebounds to lead East Tennessee State to a 103-55 rout of Milligan College on Saturday. Micah Williams scored 17 points, Isiah Brown added 16, Mike Smith scored 13 and Justin Tubbs had 11 points for the Buccaneers (2-2), who took a 61-17 lead into halftime. Twelve players saw action for ETSU, which will play its next eight games on the road before returning home on Dec. 30. The Buccaneers shot 68.8 percent from the field (22 of 32), 50 percent from the 3-point line (6 of 12) and 78.6 percent from the free throw line (11 of 14) in the first half. They led 16-2 on Williams' 3-pointer with 16:22 remaining and 29-9 on J.C. Ward's two free throws with 11:11 left in the first half. Adam Sollazzo added a career-high 10 assists for ETSU. Hudson Fricke led Milligan (2-5), a NAIA program, with 18 points on six 3-pointers.
